'''Benga''' is a [[Bantu language]] spoken by the [[Benga people]] of [[Equatorial Guinea]] and [[Gabon]]. It has a dialectical variation called ''Bapuku''. Benga speakers inhabit a small coastal portion of [[Río Muni]], the Cape of San Juan, suburban enclaves of [[Rio Benito]] and [[Bata, Equatorial Guinea|Bata]], the islands of [[Corisco]], [[Elobey Chico|Small Elobey]] and [[Great Elobey]].

