The '''Bété languages''' are spoken in central-western [[Ivory Coast]]. There are many dialects but they can be grouped as follows
*Western **[[Bété of Gagnoa]] **[[Kouya language|Kouya]] *Eastern **[[Bété of Guiberoua]] **[[Bété of Daloa]] **[[Godié language|Godié]]
They belong to the [[Kru languages|Kru language]] family.
