{{Infobox language |name=Juwal |nativename=Muniwara |states=[[Papua New Guinea]] |region=[[East Sepik Province]] |speakers={{sigfig|1440|2}} |date=2000 census |ref=e18 |familycolor=Papuan |fam1=[[Torricelli languages|Torricelli]] |fam2=[[Marienberg languages|Marienberg]] |iso3=mwb |glotto=juwa1238 |glottorefname=Juwal }}
'''Juwal''' a.k.a. '''Muniwara''' is a [[Torricelli languages|Torricelli language]] of [[Papua New Guinea]]. Other names are ''Mambe'' and ''Tumara ~ Tumaru''.
