'''Language isolates and independent language families in Arunachal''' are languages in [[Arunachal Pradesh]], [[India]], traditionally classified in [[Sino-Tibetan languages]] but recently possibly being [[language isolate]]s and independent [[language family|language families]]. Blench (2011) proposed four language isolates ([[Hrusish languages|Hruso]], [[Miji languages|Miji]], [[Midzu languages|Miju]], and [[Puroik language|Puroik]]) and three independent families ([[Digaro languages|Mishmic]], [[Kho-Bwa languages|Kamengic]], and [[Siangic languages|Siangic]]).<ref>[http://www.rogerblench.info/Language/South%20Asia/NEI/General/Lingres/Declassifying%20Arunachal.pdf ''(De)classifying Arunachal languages: Reconsidering the evidence''] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130526230734/http://www.rogerblench.info/Language/South%20Asia/NEI/General/Lingres/Declassifying%20Arunachal.pdf |date=2013-05-26 }}</ref> However, this is disputed by Anderson (2014)<ref name="Anderson2014">Anderson, Gregory D.S. 2014. ''On the classification of the Hruso (Aka) language''. Paper presented at the 20th Himalayan Languages Symposium, Nanyang Technological University, Singapore.</ref> and others, who consider them to be primary branches of [[Sino-Tibetan languages|Sino-Tibetan]] rather than as isolates or independent language phyla.
==Possible language isolates and independent families== *'''[[Hrusish languages]]''' **[[Hruso language|Hruso]] **[[Miji languages]]<ref name="Blench2015">Blench, Roger. 2015. [https://www.academia.edu/12657496/The_Mijiic_languages_distribution_dialects_wordlist_and_classification ''The Mijiic languages: distribution, dialects, wordlist and classification'']. m.s.</ref>: Bangru, Eastern Miji, Western Miji *'''[[Kho-Bwa languages]]''' **[[Puroik language|Puroik]]: diverse dialects **[[Bugun language|Bugun]] **Western Kho-Bwa ***[[Sherdukpen language|Sherdukpen]], [[Sartang language|Sartang]] ***[[Chug language|Chug]] (Duhumbi), [[Lishpa language|Lish]] (Khispi) *'''[[Siangic languages]]''' **[[Koro language (India)|Koro]] **[[Milang language|Milang]] *'''[[Miju languages]]''' **[[Miju language|Miju]] (Kman) **[[Meyor language|Meyor]] (Zakhring) *'''[[Digaro languages]]''' **[[Idu Mishmi language|Idu]] **[[Taraon language|Taraon]]
